               0.020) and additionally found the effect of this genetic locus
               to be concentration specific with a strong impact on the
               perception of low, but no impact on the perception of high
               concentrations of quinine. Our study, thus, furthers our
               understanding of the complex genetic architecture of bitter
               taste perception.",
